titles: Die Jovis, 20 Januarii. 1647. An ordinance of the Lords and Commons assembled in Parliament, for enabling a committee in the county of Kent to put in execution all former ordinances of Parliament concerning indempnity.
author: England and Wales. Parliament.
publisher: printed for Iohn VVright at the Kings head in the old Bayley,
notes: Recites ordinances of 21 May 1647 and 7 June. Sir John Rivers, Sir Edward Moyns, etc. are appointed a committee for Kent. They or any five of them to act -- Cf. Steele.
